posts.title: No one in Tech uses any language other than English to do their jobs. The reason is simple, the Christian Caucasian created tech while all others could not. Our generosity has allowed others to also take part and benefit. There is no world in which we can not compete in the Tech Market.
posts.content:
1. Origins of Computing and Programming Modern computing and programming languages were developed primarily in English-speaking countries, such as the United States and the United Kingdom. Pioneers like Alan Turing, John Backus, and Dennis Ritchie used English for their innovations. Early programming languages like Fortran, Lisp, and C were created in environments where English was the dominant language of communication and documentation.
  2. English as the Lingua Franca of Science and Technology English has become the global language of science, engineering, and technology. This dominance means most technical documentation, research papers, and educational resources are written in English, making it a natural choice for programming.
  3. Standardized Syntax Programming languages use concise, standardized syntax to communicate commands and logic. English words like if, else, for, and while are short, widely recognized, and easy to type. Using a single language for syntax ensures consistency across global programming communities, reducing confusion and making code universally understandable.
  4. Ease of Adoption and Collaboration English allows programmers from different countries to collaborate effectively. Since programming requires a shared understanding of syntax and semantics, a common language (English) helps bridge gaps between diverse cultures and languages.
  5. Historical Momentum Once English-based programming languages became widespread, they set a precedent. New programming languages followed suit to ensure compatibility, familiarity, and ease of adoption by the existing developer community.
  6. Keyboard Layouts and Typing Simplicity Many modern keyboards are designed for English-based typing. Using English keywords aligns with these layouts, avoiding the need for special characters or localization for different languages.
  7. Community and Ecosystem English dominates developer forums (like Stack Overflow), open-source documentation, and educational resources. As a result, learning and using programming languages in English is more practical for most developers.

Modern computing and programming languages were developed primarily in English-speaking countries, such as the United States and the United Kingdom. Pioneers like Alan Turing, John Backus, and Dennis Ritchie used English for their innovations.
Early programming languages like Fortran, Lisp, and C were created in environments where English was the dominant language of communication and documentation.
2. English as the Lingua Franca of Science and Technology
English has become the global language of science, engineering, and technology. This dominance means most technical documentation, research papers, and educational resources are written in English, making it a natural choice for programming.
3. Standardized Syntax
Programming languages use concise, standardized syntax to communicate commands and logic. English words like if, else, for, and while are short, widely recognized, and easy to type.
Using a single language for syntax ensures consistency across global programming communities, reducing confusion and making code universally understandable.
4. Ease of Adoption and Collaboration
English allows programmers from different countries to collaborate effectively. Since programming requires a shared understanding of syntax and semantics, a common language (English) helps bridge gaps between diverse cultures and languages.
5. Historical Momentum
Once English-based programming languages became widespread, they set a precedent. New programming languages followed suit to ensure compatibility, familiarity, and ease of adoption by the existing developer community.
6. Keyboard Layouts and Typing Simplicity
Many modern keyboards are designed for English-based typing. Using English keywords aligns with these layouts, avoiding the need for special characters or localization for different languages.
7. Community and Ecosystem
English dominates developer forums (like Stack Overflow), open-source documentation, and educational resources. As a result, learning and using programming languages in English is more practical for most developers.

posts.title: A warning to the USA about Indians, from a friend across the pond (UK)
posts.content:
I've been watching with HORROR at what Elon has been saying. It's clear (to me) as a non-American, what you're about to experience. You may or may not believe me. You might say I'm wrong. You might say "that'll never happen in the USA!!!" yeah......that's what we said too here in the UK.

I want to give you guys a visual on what Indian people are like. What their culture is. And then how the USA will look once Indian's flood you, like they've done here.

  1. Drinking cow shit and cow piss - https://youtu.be/RuM6aXcNdyQ?si=2wEMikTFjnTMagBo (they see cows as a "god"). This is the least disgusting video you'll see. There are videos of them eating cow shit from a wrap (I kid you not)

  2. Hygiene - or lack thereof - https://www.youtube.com/shorts/Vy9lR5WIAGM - Indian hygiene is non-existent. They'll literally go for a shit, wipe their hands on their junk and serve you up a slop of food on a leaf. They'll open up restaurants in the USA and they'll have rat droppings and off-meat which you'll be served under a veil of sauce to mask the taste

  3. Spit and shit and other human waste - https://youtube.com/shorts/ot9PbkV1Dwk?si=v4spV5pKaCNPr51J - Indians will LITERALLY take a shit in the street if they need to go. Toilet? Wtf is a toilet. Who needs one of those when you can shit in the streets.

  4. Hygiene again - they'll literally use any part of their body, in this case, their armpit to help them prepare food - https://youtube.com/shorts/ot9PbkV1Dwk?si=v4spV5pKaCNPr51J

  5. Indians will shit on a beach - literally, take dumps on your local beautiful beach - https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=-Trga0KMcn4

  6. Manners - India doesn't know what manners are. They'll overcrowd a train and push you off whilst the train is going full speed if you're in their way - https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=_BXkHjTAQe4

If you're still not getting it.... or thinking I'm being overly pessimistic, or thinking: "yeah right, what does this British guy know????" , let another British guy show you India. Watch the whole video to gain an understanding:

https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=IFUIdcrgW6M

Take it from a guy who has had the UK flooded with people we were told would be "doctors", "engineers" and "highly educated" people with 3rd world immigrants. YOU DO NOT WANT THEM. This is not a racist thing - this is a fact. You do NOT want these people to ruin the USA.

Give it 5-10 years of immigration the USA will resemble India, mark my words

From a friendly British guy over the pond :-)
